<br>
If you really want to make fast cash at the expense of ANY exp, here's what to do: (btw I haven't done this, it's waaaaay to boring, but a RL friend of mine does this, so it does work. Sort of)  Go to EC (or whatever your &quot;auction zone&quot; on your server is. On Fennin it's EC) with 100pp or so. Watch the auctions, and look for good deals.....like an advisor robe for 250pp. Then, auction the advisor robe for a bit higher than the &quot;normal&quot; price....the advisor robe (depending on your server) you'd try selling for about 1k to 900pp. Even buy the advisor robe it someone's selling it for 400pp or so, because you can still make a profit. NOTE: You have to KNOW what stuff is worth on your server......having a second computer that you can check EQprices.com on is really nice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
So then, when you get ~800pp for the robe, you can buy something else that's normally worth 1K or so......it's callled &quot;trading up&quot;.<br>
<br>
It sounds stupid....why would anyone sell something that's &quot;worth&quot; 500pp for 250pp? Well, they do. They may really want to sell it, and if they're offering something at the normal price, you can usually talk them down a bit if noone offers the normal price.<br>
<br>
Using this method, my RL friend has gear (as a level 30 ranger) that a level 60 would not be ashamed to own. He twinked his rouge with a sash of the dragonborn, Sebilite croaking dirk (10/18, worth almost 60k). It's insane. The only downside to this is that you don't level <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    He started his character a month before I did, and he's level 30, and I'm level 40<br>
