- Make sure you have a timer.  The wanderer is on a 16 minute timer.<br>
- Use your Fire Pet.  BOII and use your DS until he decides to cast his.<br>
- Let your pet take a beating until the yeti loses a little health twice.  Then Cinder Bolt/Blaze and finish with a CB/Blaze or Shock of Spikes depending on Yeti's health.  At 39 I think I sometimes had to use a SoS as a finisher.  I only use CB when I have the room.<br>
- Watch your pet's health.  If your pet drops below 35% health after your first DD you might consider healing him.  If the Yeti gets in a lucky shot and takes out your pet usually the yeti runs.  But if not then you die.<br>
- I never bother to buff myself unless I take too many hits and then cast Phantom Chain to get my HP back up.<br>
- Make sure you outdamage your pet. I was letting my pet solo the yetis until he needed his first heal, and then healed once and nuked.  I got much better experience with 2 nukes.<br>
